name: Frittata with Spinach and Cheese
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Sauté spinach in olive oil until wilted.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Mix in sautéed spinach and grated cheese.
Pour mixture into an oven-safe skillet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until set.
Serve warm.

name: Italian Breakfast Bruschetta
instructions: Toast the baguette slices lightly.
Dice tomatoes and mix with chopped basil, olive oil, salt and pepper.
Spoon tomato mixture over toasted bread.
Serve immediately.

name: Spaghetti Carbonara
instructions: Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water until al dente.
Sauté guanciale until crispy.
Whisk eggs with pecorino and black pepper.
Mix pasta with guanciale and egg mixture off the heat.
Serve immediately.

name: Pasta Primavera
instructions: Cook pasta until al dente.
Sauté vegetables in olive oil.
Add garlic and cook briefly.
Combine pasta with vegetables and parmesan.
Serve warm.

name: Caprese Salad
instructions: Slice tomatoes and mozzarella.
Layer tomato and mozzarella slices.
Top with basil leaves.
Drizzle olive oil and balsamic vinegar.
Serve immediately.

name: Margherita Pizza
instructions: Preheat oven to 250°C.
Roll dough and spread tomato sauce.
Top with mozzarella and basil.
Bake for 7–10 minutes.
Serve hot.

name: Osso Buco
instructions: Season and sear veal shanks.
Sauté vegetables in olive oil.
Deglaze with wine, then add broth.
Simmer covered for 1.5 hours.
Serve with gremolata.

name: Bruschetta al Pomodoro
instructions: Toast bread slices.
Mix chopped tomatoes, garlic, basil, olive oil.
Spoon mixture over toasted bread.
Serve immediately.

name: Tiramisu
instructions: Brew espresso and cool.
Beat yolks with sugar.
Fold in mascarpone.
Dip ladyfingers in espresso and layer in dish.
Spread mascarpone mixture.
Repeat layers and dust with cocoa.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

name: Panna Cotta
instructions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat cream, sugar, and vanilla until warm.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Pour into molds and refrigerate 4 hours.
Top with berries and serve.

name: Congee (Rice Porridge)
instructions: Rinse rice thoroughly.
Bring water to boil, add rice and salt.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until thick and creamy.
Adjust seasoning and garnish with spring onions.

name: Kung Pao Chicken
instructions: Dice chicken and marinate with soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir-fry chicken until browned.
Add vegetables, garlic, chili paste, and vinegar.
Toss in peanuts and cook for another 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

name: Vegetable Chow Mein
instructions: Boil noodles according to package instructions and drain.
Sauté vegetables in sesame oil with garlic.
Add soy sauce and stir-fry noodles with vegetables.
Cook for 5 minutes, tossing frequently.
Serve hot.

name: Sweet and Sour Shrimp
instructions: Coat shrimp lightly with cornstarch.
Fry shrimp until pink and cooked.
Stir-fry peppers, then add vinegar, sugar, and soy sauce.
Toss shrimp back in and coat evenly.
Serve immediately.

name: Peking Duck
instructions: Marinate duck with honey, soy sauce, and five spice.
Air dry duck overnight for crispy skin.
Roast in oven at 190°C for 1.5–2 hours.
Slice thinly and serve with pancakes, hoisin, and onions.

name: Mapo Tofu
instructions: Brown pork in oil.
Add chili bean paste and garlic, stir-fry until fragrant.
Add tofu cubes and soy sauce, simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle Sichuan peppercorns and serve.

name: Spring Rolls
instructions: Sauté vegetables in sesame oil and soy sauce.
Let mixture cool completely.
Fill wrappers and roll tightly.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with sweet chili sauce.

name: Egg Tarts
instructions: Preheat oven to 200°C.
Roll puff pastry into tart molds.
Whisk yolks, sugar, milk, and vanilla.
Fill tarts and bake 20–25 minutes until golden.
Cool before serving.

name: Sesame Balls (Jian Dui)
instructions: Mix rice flour and water into a dough.
Fill with red bean paste and roll into balls.
Coat with sesame seeds.
Deep fry until golden and crisp.
Cool slightly before serving.

name: Steamed Sponge Cake (Ma Lai Gao)
instructions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Fold in flour, baking powder, and oil.
Pour batter into steamer-safe pan.
Steam for 30 minutes until spongy.
Cool before slicing.

name: Manakish Zaatar (Zaatar Flatbread)
instructions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and warm water to form a soft dough; knead 8–10 minutes.
Let dough rest and rise for 30–45 minutes (optional for quicker 20 min proof).
Mix zaatar and olive oil into a paste.
Divide dough into rounds, roll thin, brush with zaatar mixture.
Bake at 240°C (460°F) for 8–10 minutes until edges are golden.
Serve warm.

name: Labneh Plate with Olive Oil & Zaatar
ingredients: Olives and fresh mint for garnish
instructions: Spoon labneh onto a shallow serving plate and spread slightly.
Drizzle olive oil generously over the labneh.
Sprinkle zaatar and garnish with cucumber, tomatoes, olives and mint.
Serve with warm pita or fresh vegetables.

name: Foul Medames (Stewed Fava Beans)
ingredients: Chopped parsley and chopped tomatoes to garnish
instructions: Warm olive oil in a saucepan; sauté garlic briefly without burning.
Add fava beans, a splash of water, cumin, salt and pepper; simmer 10–15 minutes.
Mash slightly for a rustic texture.
Finish with lemon juice and garnish with parsley and tomatoes.
Serve warm with pita bread.

name: Tabbouleh
instructions: Soak bulgur 10 minutes in cold water, squeeze out excess moisture.
Combine chopped parsley, mint, tomato and onion in a bowl.
Add bulgur, lemon juice, olive oil and salt; toss well.
Adjust seasoning and chill briefly before serving.

name: Fattoush Salad
instructions: Toast pita until crisp and break into bite-sized pieces.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, radish and parsley in a large bowl.
Whisk pomegranate molasses, olive oil, lemon juice, sumac and salt.
Pour dressing over salad, add pita pieces, toss and serve immediately.

name: Shawarma (Chicken) Plate
ingredients: Pickled turnips and garlic sauce to serve
instructions: Mix yogurt, olive oil, garlic, shawarma spices, cumin, salt and pepper; marinate chicken 1–3 hours.
Grill or pan-sear chicken until fully cooked and slightly charred (6–8 min per side depending on thickness).
Slice thinly and serve with rice or on a plate with pickled turnips and garlic sauce.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

name: Kibbeh Bil Sanieh (Baked Kibbeh)
instructions: Soak bulgur 10 minutes, drain and squeeze out moisture.
Process half the bulgur with half the meat to make a smooth paste; season with salt and spices.
Sauté chopped onion and remaining meat; add pine nuts and season—this is the filling.
Spread half the meat-bulgur mixture in a baking dish, spread filling, and top with remaining mixture.
Score top, brush with olive oil and bake at 180 °C (350 °F) for 35–45 minutes until cooked through.
Slice and serve warm with yogurt or salad.

name: Sayadiyah (Fish with Spiced Rice)
ingredients: 800g firm white fish fillets (cod or sea bass)
1 tsp baharat or fish spice blend
instructions: Sauté onions in olive oil until deeply caramelized and set aside.
Season fish with baharat, turmeric, salt and pepper; pan-fry until cooked and golden; flake into large pieces.
Cook rice in fish or vegetable stock until tender.
Stir caramelized onions into rice and fold in flaked fish gently.
Serve hot with lemon wedges and chopped parsley.

name: Classic Hummus
instructions: Combine chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic and cumin in a food processor.
Process until smooth, adding olive oil or a bit of water to adjust texture.
Season with salt, swirl olive oil on top and garnish with paprika and parsley.
Serve with warm pita.

name: Knafeh (Cheese Pastry with Syrup)
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Prepare sugar syrup by boiling sugar and water; add lemon juice, simmer 8–10 minutes; finish with orange blossom water and cool.
Spread half the shredded phyllo in a buttered pan, press down and top with shredded cheese.
Cover with remaining phyllo, drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 25–30 minutes until golden and crisp.
Pour cooled syrup over hot knafeh, garnish with pistachios and serve warm.

name: Chilaquiles Verdes
instructions: Cut tortillas into triangles and fry until crispy.
Heat salsa verde in a pan and add tortillas.
Fry eggs sunny-side-up separately.
Top chilaquiles with eggs, sour cream, queso fresco, and cilantro.

name: Chicken Tinga Tacos
instructions: Boil and shred chicken.
Sauté onions and tomatoes, blend with chipotle and broth.
Simmer chicken in sauce for 10 minutes.
Serve on warm tortillas with cilantro and lime.

name: Vegetarian Burrito Bowl
instructions: Cook rice and season with lime juice.
Layer rice, beans, corn, avocado, and salsa.
Top with cilantro and serve.

name: Carne Asada
instructions: Marinate steak with lime juice, garlic, cilantro, cumin, salt, and pepper.
Grill to desired doneness.
Rest for 5 minutes, then slice thinly.

name: Chicken Enchiladas
instructions: Shred cooked chicken and mix with sauce.
Roll chicken in tortillas and place in a baking dish.
Top with more sauce and cheese.
Bake at 180°C for 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and cilantro.

name: Shrimp Tacos
instructions: Season shrimp and cook until pink.
Assemble tacos with slaw, shrimp, chipotle mayo, and cilantro.
Serve with lime.

name: Guacamole
instructions: Mash avocados with lime juice.
Mix in onion, tomato, jalapeño, and cilantro.
Season with salt and serve.

name: Queso Fundido
instructions: Cook chorizo and jalapeño.
Add cheese and melt.
Serve hot with tortillas.

name: Churros
instructions: Boil water, sugar, and butter.
Stir in flour, then add egg.
Pipe dough and fry until golden.
Coat in cinnamon sugar.

name: Sopapillas
instructions: Mix dry ingredients, add water, knead dough.
Roll and cut into squares.
Fry until puffed and golden.
Drizzle with honey.

name: Masala Dosa
instructions: Soak rice, dal, and fenugreek seeds overnight.
Grind to a smooth batter and ferment.
Cook potatoes with onions, mustard seeds, and curry leaves for the filling.
Spread batter on a hot tawa to form thin dosa, add filling, and fold.
Serve hot with chutney and sambar.

name: Butter Chicken
instructions: Marinate chicken in yogurt and spices for 30 minutes.
Grill or sear chicken pieces.
Cook tomato puree with butter, garlic, and spices.
Add chicken and cream, simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with naan or rice.

name: Palak Paneer
instructions: Blanch spinach and blend to a puree.
Sauté onions, tomatoes, and spices.
Add spinach puree and simmer.
Add paneer cubes and cream, cook for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with roti or naan.

name: Chole (Chickpea Curry)
instructions: Soak chickpeas overnight and cook until soft.
Sauté onions, tomatoes, and spices.
Add chickpeas and simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with cilantro and serve with bhature or rice.

name: Rogan Josh
instructions: Marinate lamb in yogurt and spices.
Brown onions and sear lamb.
Add tomato puree and simmer for 45 minutes.
Finish with garam masala and serve with naan.

name: Biryani
instructions: Marinate chicken with yogurt and spices.
Partially cook rice with whole spices.
Layer chicken and rice, drizzle saffron milk.
Cook on low heat (dum) for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with raita.

name: Paneer Butter Masala
instructions: Sauté onions and tomatoes, then blend to puree.
Cook puree with butter, spices, and cream.
Add paneer cubes and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with naan or rice.

name: Samosa
instructions: Make dough with flour and water.
Boil potatoes and peas, mash with spices.
Fill dough cones with filling and seal.
Fry until golden brown.

name: Gulab Jamun
instructions: Make dough with khoya, flour, and baking powder.
Shape into balls and fry on low heat.
Soak in sugar syrup flavored with cardamom.

name: Ladoo
instructions: Roast gram flour in ghee until golden.
Add sugar and cardamom.
Shape into balls and garnish with nuts.
